# Atlasi Place Discovery Pipeline — Spec Document

## Purpose

A Python CLI tool that discovers trending, non-obvious places in any city by scraping TikTok and Instagram via Apify, extracting place names using an LLM, deduplicating/scoring them, and storing everything in a local SQLite database. Built to feed TikTok slideshow content for the Atlasi travel app.

---

## Architecture Overview

```
CLI Input (city name)
    │
    ▼
Hashtag Generator (LLM)
    │
    ▼
Apify Scrapers (TikTok + Instagram)
    │
    ▼
Raw Post Storage (SQLite)
    │
    ▼
LLM Place Extraction
    │
    ▼
Deduplication + Scoring
    │
    ▼
Tourist Trap Filter (LLM)
    │
    ▼
Final Places Table (SQLite)
```

---

## Tech Stack

- **Language**: Python 3.11+
- **Scraping**: Apify API (via `apify-client` Python package)
- **LLM**: OpenRouter API (model configurable, default `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4`)
- **Database**: SQLite (single local file, `places.db`)
- **Config**: `.env` file for API keys

